-- As described in Gor83, The Classification of Finite Simple Groups, Volume 1: Groups of Noncharacteristic 2 Type, Daniel Gorenstein


/-

X: Grp

Theorem [ (
  (O(X) = 1) AND (Syl2 X is connected)
) -> (
  (X is of characteristic 2 type) OR (X is of component type)
) ]


equiv.

Theorem [
  (O(X) = 1)
-> (
  (X is of characteristic 2 type) OR (X is of component type) OR NOT (Syl2 X is connected)
) ]

-/
